Australia, N.Z. Stocks: BHP, Equinox, Mesoblast, Newcrest, Rio

-- B y   S h a n i   R a j a
-- 
2011-03-04T05:55:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-03/australia-n-z-stocks-bhp-equinox-newcrest-st-barbara.html
Australia’s S&P/ASX 200 Index
climbed 1.2 percent to 4,864.30 as of the 4:10 p.m. close, its
highest level since Feb. 21. The measure advanced 0.6 percent
this week. New Zealand’s  NZX 50 Index (NZSE50FG)  rose 0.6 percent to
3,418.11 in Wellington.  The following were among the most active shares in the
market today. Stock symbols are in parentheses after company
names.  Mining companies: Copper rose to a two-week high in London
yesterday as the Arab League weighed a proposal from Venezuela’s  Hugo Chavez  to mediate the conflict in Libya.    BHP Billiton Ltd. (BHP)  , the world’s No. 1 mining
company, gained 1.5 percent to A$47.25. Rio Tinto Group (RIO AU),
the world’s third-largest mining company, rose 1.6 percent to
A$85.52.        Equinox Minerals Ltd. (EQN)   gained 0.7 percent to A$5.82.
The copper mining company seeking to buy Lundin Mining Corp. for
C$4.8 billion ($4.9 billion) said it wants to refinance the $3.2
billion debt it’s using for the deal within three months.    Mesoblast Ltd. (MSB)   jumped 9.1 percent, taking its
advance for the week to 22 percent, to A$6.33 after Standard &
Poor’s said it will add the developer of stem-cell treatments to
its S&P/ASX 300 Index.    Newcrest Mining Ltd. (NCM)  , Australia’s biggest gold
producer, gained 4.7 percent to A$40.02 after the mining company
nearly doubled the estimated size of a gold deposit in  Papua New
Guinea .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shani Raja in Sydney at   sraja4@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editors responsible for this story:
Nick Gentle at   ngentle2@bloomberg.net . 